11

00:00:32,760  -->  00:00:35,480
Booleans are the simplest type of data.

12

00:00:35,480  -->  00:00:38,715
They can only be true or false.

13

00:00:38,715  -->  00:00:41,530
Think about if you're holding a pencil in your hand.

14

00:00:41,530  -->  00:00:44,785
You either are or you aren't holding that pencil.

15

00:00:44,785  -->  00:00:46,210
Think about a light switch.

16

00:00:46,210  -->  00:00:48,530
It's either on or off.

17

00:00:48,530  -->  00:00:52,515
One tricky thing to remember about Booleans is that they are case sensitive.

18

00:00:52,515  -->  00:00:58,370
Always make sure to use a T for true and a F for false.

19

00:00:58,370  -->  00:01:00,980
When using them, they look like this.

20

00:01:00,980  -->  00:01:06,050
Booleans are often used to control the flow of a program, such as in loops.

21

